HEADWORD: Nightcap
<hw>Night"cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cap
worn in bed to protect the head, or in undress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An alcoholic beverage drunk at bedtime.</def>
<mark>[Cant]</mark> <rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nightclothes</ent>⟦br⟧
